metadata:
  section_id: 20
  hadith_first: 11420
  hadith_last: 11431

hadiths[12]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}: 11420,"The Prophet (along with his companions) reached Mecca in the morning of the fourth of Dhul-Hijja assuming Ihram for Hajj only. So when we arrived at Mecca, the Prophet ﷺ ordered us to change our intentions of the Ihram for ʿUmra and that we could finish our Ihram after performing the ʿUmra and could go to our wives (for sexual intercourse). The people began talking about that. Jabir said surprisingly, ""Shall we go to Mina while semen is dribbling from our male organs?"" Jabir moved his hand while saying so. When this news reached the Prophet ﷺ he delivered a sermon and said, ""I have been informed that some peoples were saying so and so; By Allah I fear Allah more than you do, and am more obedient to Him than you. If I had known what I know now, I would not have brought the Hadi (sacrifice) with me and had the Hadi not been with me, I would have finished the Ihram."" At that Suraqa bin Malik stood up and asked ""O Messenger of Allah ﷺ! Is this permission for us only or is it forever?"" The Prophet ﷺ replied, ""It is forever."" In the meantime ʿAli bin Abu Talib came from Yemen and was saying Labbaik for what the Prophet ﷺ has intended. (According to another man, ʿAli was saying Labbaik for Hajj similar to Messenger of Allah ﷺ's). The Prophet ﷺ told him to keep on the Ihram and let him share the Hadi with him. (Using translation from Bukhārī 2505)",,, 11421,"""The Messenger of Allah,  ﷺ , participate in the sacrifice.""",,, 11422,"He was a partner of the Prophet ﷺ in the early days of Islam in trade. So, on the day of conquest, he said, ""Welcome to my brother and partner, do not cover up or hide.""",,, 11423,"I came to the Prophet ﷺ. The people began to praise me and make a mention of me. The Messenger of Allah ﷺ said: I know you, that is, he knew him. I said: My father and mother be sacrificed for you! you were my partner and how good a partner ; you neither disputed nor quarrelled. (Using translation from Abū Dāʾūd 4836)",,, 11424,"The Messenger of Allah  ﷺ  said, ""Allah says, 'I am the third of the two partners as long as neither of them betrays his companion. But when one of them betrays the other, I will withdraw from between them.'"" Abu Ali Al-Roudhbary narrated to us, who told us Abu Bakr ibn Dasa, who narrated to us Abu Dawood, who narrated to us Muhammad ibn Sulaiman Al-Mississi with his chain of narrators, he said, ""Abu Hurairah narrated to me and said, 'Verily, Allah Most High says, so He mentioned it.'""",,, 11425,,,, 11426,"From his grandfather Abdullah ibn Hisham, who had met the Prophet ﷺ, his mother Zainab bint Humayd took him to the Messenger of Allah ﷺ. She said, ""O Messenger of Allah, give him your pledge of allegiance."" The Prophet ﷺ replied, ""He is still young."" Then he stroked his head and supplicated for him. He used to sacrifice one sheep for his entire family.",,, 11427,,,, 11428,"I Ammar, and Sa'd became partners in what we would receive on the day of Badr. Sa'd then brought two prisoners, but I and Ammar did not bring anything. (Using translation from Abū Dāʾūd 3388)",,, 11429,"The Prophet ﷺ said, ""Muslims are bound by their conditions."" Sufyan added in his narration, ""What is agreed upon as true from it, and we have narrated that with its addition from the hadith of Khushayf, from Urwah, from Aisha, and from Ata', from Anas bin Malik, in a marfu' form.""",,, 11430,"The Messenger of Allah  ﷺ  said, ""Muslims are bound by their conditions, except for a condition that prohibits what is permissible or allows what is prohibited."" Abu Bakr ibn al-Harith al-Faqih narrated to us, who informed us that Abu Muhammad ibn Hayyan narrated to him, that Abu Isa al-Khutuli narrated to him, who narrated from Abdullah ibn Muhammad al-Azrami, who narrated from Marwan ibn Muawiyah, who mentioned it likewise.",,, 11431,,,,
